{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878314764,"sessionID":"ses_28569c600ffe4YuLfmwTvderhz","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9647f3001p7ibb5VDGgdW3c","messageID":"msg_d7a963b04001ByzOSN4IKj24x2","sessionID":"ses_28569c600ffe4YuLfmwTvderhz","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_2b83f8b5ac23401cbddc73ca","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Find AR-033 Makefile changes","prompt":"Search the workspace thoroughly for any files related to \"AR-033\", \"Makefile\", \"agentcube\", or build targets. Look for:\n1. Any archive/change tracking files (like CHANGELOG.md, ARCHIVE.md, or similar)\n2. Makefile or Makefile-related files\n3. Any documentation about build targets\n4. Git history or commit messages mentioning AR-033 or Makefile build targets\n5. Any project structure files that might indicate what was done\n\nSearch in:\n- /home/dsj/benchmark (the workspace root)\n- Any subdirectories\n\nReturn ALL findings including file paths, relevant content snippets, and any indication of what was completed vs deferred for this change.","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28569a5b4ffe4shhyudefTSpDv (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nHere is a comprehensive report of all findings related to AR-033, Makefile, agentcube, and build targets.\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE FINDINGS REPORT\n\n### 1. CONTEXT: What This Workspace Is\n\nThis is an **SDD-TEE v5.1** (Specification-Driven Development Token Efficiency Evaluation) benchmark framework. It evaluates AI coding assistants by having them implement the open-source [agentcube](https://github.com/ShijunDeng/agentcube) project (a Kubernetes-native sandbox orchestration platform) through a structured 8-stage SDD workflow. The project is decomposed into 43+ granular ARs (Allocated Requirements).\n\n---\n\n### 2. AR-033: Makefile Build Target System\n\n**AR-033** is titled **\"Makefile 构建目标体系\"** (Makefile Build Target System). It is a **root-module, Makefile-language, Medium-size** change request.\n\n#### 2.1 AR-033 Spec Files (Current Workspace)\n\n| File | Path | Status |\n|------|------|--------|\n| **proposal.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/proposal.md` | **FULLY POPULATED** (161 lines) |\n| **delta-spec.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/delta-spec.md` | **FULLY POPULATED** (358 lines, 16 requirements, 38+ scenarios) |\n| **design.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/design.md` | **EMPTY TEMPLATE** (57 lines, all TODO placeholders) |\n| **tasks.md** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/changes/AR-033/tasks.md` | **EMPTY TEMPLATE** (32 lines, all TODO placeholders) |\n\n#### 2.2 AR-033 Makefile Implementation\n\n| File | Path | Lines | Status |\n|------|------|-------|--------|\n| **Makefile** | `/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/Makefile` | 186 | **IMPLEMENTED** |\n\nThe Makefile header reads:\n```\n# AgentCube -- Makefile 构建目标体系\n# AR-033: Unified build, test, docker, lint, helm, and python targets\n```\n\n#### 2.3 Makefile Build Targets Implemented\n\n**Variables (7):** `TAG`, `REGISTRY`, `GOOS`, `GOARCH`, `BIN_DIR`, `LDFLAGS`, `VERBOSE`\n\n**Go Build Targets:**\n- `make build` -- compiles all 4 binaries (router, workloadmanager, agentd, picod) to `bin/`\n- `make build/router`, `make build/workloadmanager`, `make build/agentd`, `make build/picod`\n- `make clean` -- removes `bin/` directory\n\n**Docker Build Targets:**\n- `make docker` -- builds all 3 images (agentcube, router, picod)\n- `make docker/agentcube`, `make docker/router`, `make docker/picod`\n- Supports `TAG` and `REGISTRY` variable overrides\n\n**Test Targets:**\n- `make test` -- runs `go test ./...`\n- `make test-coverage` -- generates `coverage.out`\n- `make test-chart` -- runs `bash test/chart/test_render.sh`\n\n**Code Quality Targets:**\n- `make lint` -- runs `golangci-lint run` (fails if tool missing)\n- `make fmt` -- runs `go fmt ./...`\n- `make vet` -- runs `go vet ./...`\n\n**Helm Targets:**\n- `make helm-lint` -- runs `helm lint` on chart dir (fails if helm missing)\n- `make helm-template` -- runs `helm template` (read-only)\n\n**Python Targets (graceful degradation):**\n- `make python-lint` -- runs ruff or flake8 if available; warns and succeeds if not\n- `make python-test` -- runs pytest if available; warns and succeeds if not\n\n**Composite Targets:**\n- `make all` -- equivalent to `make build test lint`\n- `make ci` -- equivalent to `make build test test-coverage lint helm-lint`\n\n**Phony Declarations:** All 21 targets declared `.PHONY`\n\n---\n\n### 3. Verification Report (ST-6 Stage)\n\nThe verification stage (ST-6) produced a **PASS** verdict. All **27 spec requirements** were marked as fully implemented:\n\n```\nVerdict: PASS -- All 27 spec requirements are fully implemented.\nIssues Found: None\n```\n\nKey verification findings:\n- All 7 variables defined with correct defaults\n- All build targets compile correct `./cmd/<name>` paths to `$(BIN_DIR)/<name>`\n- All docker targets use correct Dockerfiles and apply TAG/REGISTRY\n- All test targets execute correct commands\n- lint/helm-lint properly fail with clear messages when tools are missing\n- python-lint/python-test gracefully degrade (warn + exit 0) when tools absent\n- Composite targets (`all`, `ci`) chain dependencies correctly\n- All 21 targets declared `.PHONY`\n- Build failure propagation works via Make's default sequential behavior\n\n---\n\n### 4. What Was Completed vs Deferred\n\n#### COMPLETED:\n| Component | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **proposal.md** | Fully written with purpose, scope, architecture summary, impact analysis, alternatives considered, upstream dependencies |\n| **delta-spec.md** | Fully written with 16 requirements and 38+ BDD acceptance scenarios |\n| **Makefile** | Fully implemented (186 lines) with all specified targets |\n| **Verification (ST-6)** | All 27 requirements verified as PASS |\n\n#### DEFERRED / NOT COMPLETED:\n| Component | Details |\n|-----------|---------|\n| **design.md** | Empty template -- all 7 sections contain `<!-- TODO -->` placeholders |\n| **tasks.md** (in AR-033 dir) | Empty template -- all sections contain `<!-- TODO -->` placeholders |\n\nNote: A separate `tasks.md` was created at `/home/dsj/benchmark/tasks.md`, but it is for a **different AR-033 interpretation** (Python SDK -- Clients and Exceptions, not the Makefile). This appears to be a cross-contamination from the benchmark's PLAN.md which maps AR-033 to \"python-sdk / SDK clients and exception hierarchy\" -- a different AR-033 than the Makefile one in the workspace.\n\n---\n\n### 5. Archive/Change Tracking Files\n\n**No CHANGELOG.md, ARCHIVE.md, STATUS.md, VERIFICATION.md, or REPORT files were found** anywhere in the workspace. The only tracking mechanism is the SDD stage log files.\n\n---\n\n### 6. Benchmark Run Log Files for AR-033\n\n**Current workspace run** (`opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus`):\n| Log File | Path |\n|----------|------|\n| ST-0 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-033_ST-0.log` |\n| ST-1 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-033_ST-1.log` |\n| ST-2 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-033_ST-2.log` |\n| ST-3 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-033_ST-3.log` |\n| ST-4 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/AR-033_ST-4.log` |\n| ST-6 | `/home/dsj/benchmark/results/runs/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z_logs/